<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
OK. for you people that love to argue and flame every post you see.... Don't read this.   This post is intended to generate ideas and thoughts that would make BST more attractive in 50+ zones and add to the uniqueness of the class.  This was copy and pasted from what I wrote in the feign death post and thought it worthy for all to read if they wish to do so.<BR>---------------------------------------------<BR>Now the 1st thing about how to prove in roleplay why beastlord should have FD. Well, some just don't by the "play possum" things. OK let me ring off a few more that come to mind. TURTLES, PORCUPINES, both of which roll into a defensive ball or shell to lose the agro on most critters that attack them. Plus you have other animals such as lizards and snakes (cobra's) that expand and itimidate it's attacker to run them off. The blowfish that puffs up to enormous size so that it cant' be eaten and swollowed. The skunk that sprays a very offensive odor to chase many attackers away. So as you see there are a number of animals that have good defensive skills for protection. Especially the Cameleon which hides by changing it's color.<P>Therefore, lets NOT have feigh death then, but something complete different then any other class.. A brand NEW skill for BST only.<P>How about these:<BR>1)  Shell Skill (mimics a turtle, possum or porcupine): which is a clickable skill that allows you to fall on the ground in a devensive nature and AC is temporarily increased by 20 points and agro is NOT lost till 10 seconds later. This would mimic a mob attacking us then after 10 seconds lose interest in us and move along.<P>2) Camo Skill: (mimics many reptile that change color to hides it's ID from attackers) This would give the same effect as Hide or Invis, but since it's not a spell or skill that makes you disappear, but only blends you into the surroundings. Those mobs that can see thru invis would not detect you. SPECIAL skill.<P>3) Intimidate Skill: (mimics a lizzard's or snakes ability to take a posture that intimidating to it's attacker) This would be very similar to fear but is a clickable skill. The skill could get resisted, and duration is variable, but it would all depend on the level of the player and the mobs that is attacking it. BTW.. if this skill works it also has a good chance of clearing the agro list too. Example: 35th level BST sits and meds, then is jumped by a blue mob. If he is unable to deal with this mob due to health and mana, he can use this skill to attempt to fear him off and lose the agro on him. Phew>> I have no idea how you want to work the numbers, but it can be so that it's maybe 50% effective on blue mobs. If this was a green mob then their is even a higher chance of success depending on level difference. Furthermore, while the fear is in effect you can not run behind it wacking it without breaking the fear immediately and gaining agro again. And any add on mobs in a fight can work the same way. YOU Intimidate it away. You can further make this skill so that reload time is not as quick as a FD reload. <P>I like my last option the best because it fall directly in line with roleplay aspects the most. This is why lions, panthers, wolves growl and roar. INTIMIDATION.. why many reptiles (cobra's and some dragon lizzies) change posture. INTIMIDATION>> <P>Hell, there are many animals, insects that even such as peacoc*s, butterflies, and the like that have special defensive skills that are somewhat intimidating or mezmerizing in nature.<P>There you go.. NONE are current skills in the game but something NEW that falls directly into a beastlord's nature of roleplaying and is unique since those that say BST are a special hybrid are happy too.<BR>I see no problem giving the BST even more then one of these skills. Why not have both the Camo skill and Intimidate.. This would make BST very viable and special in the high end game as well since his camo ability would not be compromized by mobs that "see invis".. makes him excellent in stalking a mob undetected (without fighting unless he choose so), or just plain scouting for mobs or corpse recoveries, and the Intimidate would be very useful as well.<P>Think about how may animals and such in nature that are able to move about stalking or otherwise almost completely undetected, or can be quite defensive in nature to avoid a fight in most circumstances. <P>--------------------------------------------<P>That was part of my post which I thought would be interesting and a good topic for thought.. if you would like to add new idea's for skills or edit the 3 existing ones I already did.. feel free to do, but don't flame..
</FONT>
