Again I ask you not to flame on this post for the sake of flaming unless you have some factual input in which you can explain why or why not those skills listen now or later would OVERPOWER a class.<P>Could you please explain to me how 30 second  "Speed Skill" that reloads every 10 minutes would overpower me? If you look at the data of SOW and the increase speed it gives you, you would see that by 30th level and getting 5 points per level your "speed skill" would be 155.  This means you get 75% increase movement speed. Is this much more then what SOW gives you?  I think not.  Heck if some shaman gave you sow at 15th level you would actually be faster then that then "speed skill" which would only give you 40% increase at that level.  See as you say, I don't see how this would make us ubber or overpowering?<P>Camo Skill?  How does this make us overpowering?  The ONLY, and I mean ONLY advantage it would give ya is that it protects you from those that see thru invis.  Again I would have this skill tied directly into skill points per level.  Therefore again at lower levels a spell casted on you by another player would be much better then what your skill could give ya.  You can have it so that Camo Skill is on a ration so that at a 200 skill cap he can only maintain his "undetection" for 5 minutes fixed and again have it on a 10 minute reload.  How would this make him overpowering?  I need examples.<P>Intimidation skill:  How does this make us overpowering?  Give examples.. Let me give you an easy formula how this would be put in the game.  Even conned mobs gives you a 50/50 chance of sucess.  For each level below or above the percentage changes accordingly.  Hence a 35th level BST that was attacked by a 5th level newbie wolf would have 50+30=80% chance of success. That same 35th BST attacked by a 50th level mob he would have a 50-15=35% chance of success.  Since the reload would be, maybe 10 seconds, I don't see how this is going to make us overpowering.  In the above examples I have given, I can easily disperse the annoying wolf, where as with the RED mob I might have a 35% of escape. If I was suceessful in the first attempt.. PHEW. thank god.. if not. I have to wait 10 more seconds to retry and guess what? That RED mob is still beating me to death.  In a period of 10 seconds he'll have approx 4 rounds of whacking on me.  How long do you think I would stay alive to have a second chance? <P>None of the above skills mention above are honestly OFFENSIVE in nature and would not give us any overpowering abilit to group or solo better. Am I going to use "speed" while grouped.. NO..  Am I going to use "camo" while grouped..  ONLY for scouting, and corpse recovery.. but the moment you summon corpse or attack something, you are no longer hidden.  Am I going to use "Intimidate" while grouped.. NO<P>And I believe for the most part, 90% of the time, you arent' going to use these new skills soloing either, unless to just practice and raise them up in points.<P>However, will these skills help in the 50+ zones in groups or raids.. YOU bet they will, but they will not take away from other classes abilities or rolls in the game.<P>Again, lets try to be productive here and not just CRY "overpower" with no information or scenarios why it is.   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">
