hmm... i sounded a little rash... let me explain where i'm coming from:<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR> Could you please explain to me how 30 second "Speed Skill" that reloads every 10 minutes would overpower me? <HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Ok--this sounds quite a bit to me like Spirit of Cheetah--only problem is that it would be better than Spirit of Cheetah--SoC has a 15 minute recast time... this skill would have 10 min recast time, but wouldn't take up a spell jewel and wouldn't cost mana (though the mana for SoC is only 20 and therefore negligible, it's still worth noting).  I think that this is, in essence, a sure-fire "get-out-of-death-free" skill... make it a 1/day skill and i'd be a bit more open to it.<P><BR> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR> Intimidation skill: How does this make us overpowering? Give examples.. Let me give you an easy formula how this would be put in the game. Even conned mobs gives you a 50/50 chance of sucess. For each level below or above the percentage changes accordingly. Hence a 35th level BST that was attacked by a 5th level newbie wolf would have 50+30=80% chance of success. That same 35th BST attacked by a 50th level mob he would have a 50-15=35% chance of success. Since the reload would be, maybe 10 seconds, I don't see how this is going to make us overpowering. In the above examples I have given, I can easily disperse the annoying wolf, where as with the RED mob I might have a 35% of escape. If I was suceessful in the first attempt.. PHEW. thank god.. if not. I have to wait 10 more seconds to retry and guess what? That RED mob is still beating me to death. In a period of 10 seconds he'll have approx 4 rounds of whacking on me. How long do you think I would stay alive to have a second chance? <P>None of the above skills mention above are honestly OFFENSIVE in nature <BR> <HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>What would the duration be on this "fear" effect?--sounds to me an aweful lot like a way to fear kite, and fear kiting would offer a distinct offensive advantage which in my mind would constitute a heavy unbalancing.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR> Camo Skill? How does this make us overpowering? The ONLY, and I mean ONLY advantage it would give ya is that it protects you from those that see thru invis. Again I would have this skill tied directly into skill points per level. Therefore again at lower levels a spell casted on you by another player would be much better then what your skill could give ya. You can have it so that Camo Skill is on a ration so that at a 200 skill cap he can only maintain his "undetection" for 5 minutes fixed and again have it on a 10 minute reload. How would this make him overpowering? I need examples. <HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Hmm... not sure i understand this one properly--do you mean that this is a type of invisibility that works *only* against stuff that can see invisible?  Could a Young Grizzly Bear see through this, for instance?  If so, im not sure that it's all that useful.  That is why I assumed that it would essentially be like uber-invisibility when you proposed it.<P>If you did mean, in fact, to suggest an invisibility that worked on absolutelty every mob in EQ, it is distinctly overpowering.<P>In fact, even if it only made you invisible to mobs that could see invisible, it's overpowering.  Cast invisbility on yourself and then use this skill.  Nothing can attack you.  Zero risk = unfair.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR> Shell Skill (mimics a turtle, possum or porcupine): which is a clickable skill that allows you to fall on the ground in a devensive nature and AC is temporarily increased by 20 points and agro is NOT lost till 10 seconds later. This would mimic a mob attacking us then after 10 seconds lose interest in us and move along. <HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>In regard to this, well, i disliked this one b/c i don't want us to have FD because.<P>I think that you have to look at these skills and combine them with the skills already innate to the BL class--you have to look at the whole package assuming that you added these to the class...<BR>With these the BL would have<BR>1) spirit of wolf<BR>2) flash of light<BR>3) something akin to FD<BR>4) spirit of cheetah but lower refresh time<BR>5) uber-camo<BR>6) something akin to instill doubt<P>Now... no class in EQ can combine all of those abilities.  I'm not saying simply that "just b/c it's never been done before means that we shouldn't do it"... what i'm saying is that there's a <I>there's a reason why no other class has all these skills together</I><P>That reason is that it's <I>too safe</I>.  How the heck would you kill that class?  He can make sure that he's never agro'd, if he is he can run away with SoW, if he wants to stay and fight he can fear kite you, if things get out of hand and you run faster than sow he can use spirit of cheetah!  What mob can compete with that?<P>Most classes have 1 or 2 abilities to get out of death.<P>My druid has speed increasing spells (wolf form, sow, scale of wolf, and spirit of cheetah) in conjuncture with speed reducing spells (the snare line).  If that's not a good option he can use root and gate.  He can come up with some combination of the above strategies as well.<P>This BL has too many ways out of death: he can flee by:<P>1) send pet at mob and run with sow<BR>2) fear mob and run with sow<BR>3) just plain run with spirit of cheetah<BR>4) use the FD type one<P>I honestly think that, if these skills were to truly be as defensive as you claim they were, even that would be too much of an advantage.<P>Not to mention the fact that some of these (mainly the FD type one) would be near impossible to program and not worth VI's time.<P>So here's my compromise...<P>1) no instill doubt (i don't want fear kiting<P>2) no FD thing (too safe in combination with skills already in place)<P>3) you can have the Camo type one (just be careful not to piss off Druids) under the following conditions--> make it a skill similar to the Druid one in the Class AA skills section--can't make you invis to mobs that see invis though b/c that just defeats the purpose of those mobs<P>If you were to get any of the other ones for the class, i would want them to be class AA skills or i'd want them to at least take up spell jewels.<P>--------------------<P>and that's all i have to say about that<P>Lieflier Arctica - Halfling druid of the Wizened Aspen Grove of Karana of the 35th Equinox
