How did I know that this thread would turn into another flaming thread by those that just can't simply read the words that are written, instead of them adding words or thoughts that aren't there?  <P>Did I say mage/necro's would lose 30% damage. NO, I did not.  I said  mage/necro are still 70% of of WHO they are without their pet.  You ASSumed I was talking damage dealing. I was not.  Both Necro's and Mages have things to offer a 50+ group without their pets. Can a Mage/Necro still cause serious damage in a group without their pet?  YES.  Can a mage/necro offer other things to a group besides DD/dots.... YES<P>Whereas Beastlords are more crippled then any pet class in the game without their pet. This is fact and not disputed.  A Beastlord has only 2 things he can offer any groups beyond 50th level when his pet is dead, or not allowed.     1) dual wield and kick, and 2) a lousey 80point evoc spell. Both of which would get yourself sitting on the bench waiting to be called in after all the other choices are depleted.<P>Our DoT's will not be used (like you are ever going to see a RAID without alteast ONE shaman there) Our buffs will not be used (same reason above)  Our slow spell will not be used (same reason above).  Beastlords are gimped in the spell line up because of stacking issues incase you forgot.  OH. and PLEASE don't count the 59th level DD spell for 430, that is a bit late in the game to enjoy it for long.  <IMG SRC="frown.gif" border="0"><P>Most of you keep flaming away that Defense or Alternate skills are NOT viable, yet you push for defining skills on the offensive nature.  We do not need anymore offesive skill to deal out more damage that is already there.  We are already at 80% of what a monk can do, which is fine with me.  All I like to see done offensively is just simply redistribute that so that instead of pet+bst=80% monk damage,,, you get 'no pet'+bst=70% monk damage..  IF you don't like that, well TOO BAD.  The facts still havent' changed about the high end game that BST pets (along with other pets) are too weak and vulnerable to ripo's, area spells.  If you don't want my suggestion of making the pet buff self casting.. FINE.. then just simply make a WHOLE new spell that is a pet buff that protect the pet from those problems.<P>As for the goofball that suggest fear kiting, you are so totally wrong.  OMG I can't believe someone even suggested that. Why in the hell do you think rogues don't fear kite using ID. It's suicidal!!!!! The odds of it running into other mobs that will agro is not worth the risk. Rogues will only use ID towards the end of the fight when its weaken, flash of light will not do any good becasue at that point in the game the pet has too much agro for the mob to turn... NEXT.  BTW.. I was in Stonebrunt not long ago with my beastlord taking on the kobold camps..and this is what happens.:<P>I see Shaman Kobold and target.  Cast flash of light (I use this spell because it DOES NOT AGRO surrounding mobs) If I used slow or dot any other mobs within agro range of what I targeted comes as well.. NOT a good idea, hense flash of light.  At this point the shaman does one of two things. 1) cast back immediately where as I take damage and pet agro's and I have to do "pet back off".. This works in most cases.  2) mob runs, NOT in fear, only because he's BLIND and cant' find me.   I have had numerous times where I have casted flash of light and the mob starts to run off in a direction and stops and cast. My pet has gone agro and I was unable to repeatively back him off. SINCE I have not done ONE point of damage yet my agro is virtually NOTHING, and with the first attack of my pet that mob stops, turns and fights my pet, EVEN tho flash of light has NOT worn off....... NOW explain that?    SO where does this fear kiting you suggest come from?  I've played my class for a long time and I've never seen my pet chase and bite a mob running off after flash of light landed?  UNLESS your pet was chasing him and was NOT able to hit it one time , therefore the mob didn't agro in return. ROFLMAO<P>BTW Tan.. did I not say instead of double attack you could add a built in haste to compensate that..... DOH.. are haste spells not in the game anymore?  This was my point, is you take one thing that you dont' like and run with it without looking at the complete picture.  STOP flaming with nonsense and read before typing..   And when did we start comparing bards,necro's and druids to beastlords?  I have news for you SON.... but all three you just mention are way more valuable to a INDOOR zone group then a beastlord without pet.  EVEN the necro and mage are still more powerful and have more to offer a group without their pets then a beastlord is without his.<P>I can't believe you are even going there.. ARE YOU SAYING beastlords without pets are just as powerful as MAGES, NECROS, CHANTERS, SHAMANS, SK's (pet classes) without pets.  What planet you are from? All those classes can still ROCK the house and add alot to a group without their pets, where as we are limited to 3 attacks and a minor DD spell.  COUGH, COUGH..<P>By the way since I've never played a Chanter or Bard and I don't get into researching them,  Don't they have Haste/Slow spells and do they STACK with the low level beastlord version?   IF they don't then I assume again a beastord could only use his spells if a Shaman, Chanter, Bard is not in the group already.  Like I'm going to see that many groups in high level zones that doesn't have atleast one of the 3.
