nce I've never played a Chanter or Bard and I don't get into researching them, Don't they have Haste/Slow spells and do they STACK with the low level beastlord version?<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Slows do not stack, period.  Spell hastes do not stack except for two bard songs, at levels 52 and 60.<P>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>IF they don't then I assume again a beastord could only use his spells if a Shaman, Chanter, Bard is not in the group already.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Hybrids, actually casters in general, suffer from some overlap and have to coordinate their spells.  Bards have to change their song selection when an enchanter or shaman is present.  Rangers have to alter their strategy when a druid is present.  Shadowknights are extremely limited in what they can cast when a necromancer is present.  Paladins aren't so much affected by the presence of a cleric, as they generally cast stuns in combat.  The same is true of beastlords...so what's your point?  Are you just whining because this is your first hybrid?<P>--------------------<P>"Talk sense to a fool and he will call you foolish."   - Euripides
