Hmm, how about the fact that BL are pretty good as it is, and the skills you mention add power.  Take something that is pretty well balanced and add power to it.  That is the most succint way to say that the abilities you mention are over powering.  Doesnt really matter what the powers are.<BR>The bottom line is, BL can do some things, not others - just like all the other characters.  Is that such a bad thing?<BR>Besides, if you look carefully enough, you will notice that non casters tend to get skills, casters tend to get spells.  Classic example of that is feign death and instill doubt.  Monks get these as skills, necros get them as spells.  BL would get any such things as spells more likely than skills.  We already get invisibility spell at high level.  We already get SoW (maybe SoC should be in our list - shrug).  I think we get turtle skin (cant remember) - granted it doesnt do what you want it to, but it is a defined spell in the game.<P>On a side note, I think we should get primal avatar (after all, we are connected to the primal spirits of the animals) and Dire charm (on animals) and a death spell (animals die).  I wonder if you recognise sarcasm - just about any power could be justified through role play ideas for just about any character if you spent a bit of time thinking about it.  Just because you can do that, does not mean a power isnt imbalancing.<P>Anyway - quite a number of people have suggested the ideas would not be a good thing to give to the BL - maybe - just maybe - they are right?
