y down when using their skill.  And like what you have listed they are invisible to regular and undead mobs, but even they aren't invisible to see invis mobs.  What you are proposing would give Beastlords, the ability to not only move far faster than Rogues, but get past mobs that are all but impossible for the class, whose whole purpose is to be sneaky.  As a Rogue, I would make it my mission to get this one nerfed out of existance.  As a Beastlord, I would abuse this one so much that it would get nerfed in a matter of hours.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>As for camo? it may step on the toes of a rogue's ability in some circumstances, but not all. As for the high end game. I would much rather have a "class" on raids, especially failing ones, that can go in undetected by ANY mob and pull the corpse out with speed and reliablity. Infact if anything this would actually step on the toes of those classes that summon corpses (but NO coffin needed) The trade of is that Once you summon corpse of a fallen guild member you are visiable again but you do have the hitpoints and speed to beet ass back to the zone and drop off the corpse. I only suggest this as a high end alternative in being needed in tough zones.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>   Ummm, I fail to see the usefulness, given the limitation you place on it here.  /corpse has a range of 50 feet.  The agro range on mobs is generally 50+ feet.  Okay, so I camo, get within range of the uber mob that just killed my friends, hit /corpse, and run for the zone.  I make it about 10 steps before I get summoned and eaten for breakfast.<P>   Hmmm, Okay, so I /corpse, and immediately FD, and while I wait 10 seconds for the agro to clear, I get summoned and eaten for breakfast.<P>   Anyway, if you are going to make suggestions like these, please, please, think them through before you do.  These suggestions aren't needed to finish our class, all they do is throw up chaff and interfere with the things we really need.  Things like Valiant Companion.  Disciplines that affect our warders, class specific AA skills.<P>   And for god sakes, play a Beastlord before you try to improve it.  By your own admission in another thread, you know what Beastlords can do, because you grouped with one while playing your Druid.
