Just explaining the fact as I read them from verant and see them in action.  Do me a favor if you are so bent to believe that Verants vision is not changing for the worse.<P>Verants has admitted that SOW was a mistake on their part, in exchange more and more mobs comming into the game have sow speed. AKA Gorilla in Stonebrunt (who's speed can not be effected) Snow giffons in EW that are resistand and break root often, many new mobs such as the tribal in Luclin, the new nightshade drake? in Skyfire that is immune to snare/root... This is all verants way of making SOW less important fighting and if you fail to see that then you need to read more in the Druids/Shaman sections more often to see how this is making solo'ing that much more difficult.<P>More and More new mobs, especially in Luclin are underconned. ( read the boards ) and you'll see that more mana is required to solo these mobs, meaning more down time in medding.  Again VI is frowning upon those that solo and want to promote groups.<P>VI limits on pets that recently was exploited and changed, to include both summon and charmed pets.<P>Many key originators of EQ (Brad) and others have left VI to go elsewhere.  Will we ever get the true story about that?  VI is making changed to EQ in ways that many are not happy about (including brad and gang) and obviously the vision that Brad had differs from what VI wants now.<P>Some of VI's vision is OK but there is a purpose to everything they do such as the soul binders.. you may not believe it but that decision was strictly financial and had NOTHING to do with the game. <P>The Nerfing of illusions.  Back in the old days one used to use a variety of illusion to go to places they could not go because of faction.  NOW, VI has changed that to where ANY illusion makes you KOS reguardless. This was done so that you had to spend time to kill and gain faction, and not just simply do an illusion to bypass that.  This again was done for financial reason and not rollplay. <P>It is and will be VI's intention to make the game harder and longer to progress to keep customers paying each month. However some just get plain frustrated and leave (I have 3 good playing friends that have done exactly that) Hense "soul binders" were placed there because they felt like being nice.  Soul binders were put into the game because many "non biding" classes had a difficult time getting binds and the frustration of that was leading people to either quit the game or make a biding class to play.  <P>The only way to find out what is TRUELY going on inside VI and things are changing, (not for the better) is to talk to employees or exemployees (BRAD) and get the low down, HOWEVER, that will not happen for a period of 2 years.  Im sure every employee at VI are held under a "confidentuality" clause that prohibts them to talk about internal operations, visions, programming etc. etc. of EQ and other sister games.<P>Im sure that I'll probably be one of the first to leave EQ and go with Brad & gangs new MPORG when and if he can make it happen. I loved EQ when it first came out, however the changes in the past years are making it extremely difficult to enjoy it as much as it was in the good old days..<P>In anycase I honestly don't care if you like my views or not.  I state opinions based upon the facts I see first hand, not just cause someone says it's so. If you like the way EQ is evolving, then good for you, however Im not and niether are alot of others (Brad & gang included)..  I think with the developers of EQ leaving VI should send RED FLAGS up to everyone without blinders on.  People don't walk away from 7 figure salaries to venture into unknown territory if they are happy where they are... Common sense
