 take crossing dangerous country without Invis or Snare/Root or hunting indoors without SOW<P>In conclusion to any of you that have read this.  If you honestly sit back and look at the LOGIC you have "thumb down" others is doesn't hold water to the argument why you want high end compensation.<P>BST can solo just about as well as any other solo'ing class, however in levels past 50 the pet thing gets a little risky in more and more increasing EXP zones as you get closer to 60.  The pet dies (common on raids) you lose value to the group.  Well I have a newsflash for you.  Druids have very little importance in RAIDS with no defining roll.  With what all the HIGH END game promoters are really crying about is that they want to solo if they want just as well, but have a DESIRABLE impact too on raids.  WELL I think that is overpowering and rather spoiled.  What you are saying is that you want your cake and to eat it too...   SORRY.. NO DICE  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">    HOPE you enjoyed the reading and have reflected well on all the post on who wants what and why?<P>All I want is to have things go back to the way they used to before all these lousy crying babies starting whinning  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">
